docs.abstract: Taking an early lead in ultrafast next-generation wireless technology can give players a strategic advantage.
docs.snippet: Taking an early lead in ultrafast next-generation wireless technology can give players a strategic advantage.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Being at the forefront of a new technology often provides a strategic advantage. That helps explain why there is so much scrapping now by companies and countries over a next wave of wireless technology known as 5G.

headline.main: Why Companies and Countries Are Battling for Ascendancy in 5G
headline.print_headline: A Struggle To Shape The Future Of Wireless

docs.abstract: The company is requesting that Makan Delrahim testify in the trial over the government’s decision to block its merger with Time Warner, sources said.
docs.snippet: The company is requesting that Makan Delrahim testify in the trial over the government’s decision to block its merger with Time Warner, sources said.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — AT&T is seeking to put the head of the Justice Department’s Antitrust Division on its witness list in a trial over the government’s decision to block the phone giant’s $85 billion merger with Time Warner, according to two people with knowledge of the pretrial activity.

headline.main: AT&T Is Said to Want Antitrust Official on Witness List for Trial
headline.print_headline: AT&T Wants Rival Lawyer As a Witness

docs.abstract: John Martin, the chief executive of Turner, told a federal court that his channels were not absolutely vital for a cable or satellite business.
docs.snippet: John Martin, the chief executive of Turner, told a federal court that his channels were not absolutely vital for a cable or satellite business.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The head of Turner Broadcasting on Wednesday pushed back against one of the central arguments of the government’s case to block the AT&T and Time Warner merger, saying that his company’s channels would not be used as a weapon against rivals if the deal went through.

headline.main: Turner Chief Pushes Back on Core Justice Dept. Argument
headline.print_headline: Turner Chief Challenges U.S. Rationale for Blocking an AT&T Deal

docs.abstract: President Trump issued an order prohibiting Broadcom, a Singapore-based chip maker, from purchasing Qualcomm, citing a threat to the national security of the United States.
docs.snippet: President Trump issued an order prohibiting Broadcom, a Singapore-based chip maker, from purchasing Qualcomm, citing a threat to the national security of the United States.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Monday blocked Broadcom’s $117 billion bid for the chip maker Qualcomm, citing national security concerns and sending a clear signal that he was willing to take extraordinary measures to promote his administration’s increasingly protectionist stance.

headline.main: Trump Blocks Broadcom’s Bid for Qualcomm
headline.print_headline: Trump Blocks Overseas Takeover of Qualcomm

docs.abstract: An investigation could lead to questions that the F.C.C. chairman, Ajit Pai, has so far tried to avoid answering in public.
docs.snippet: An investigation could lead to questions that the F.C.C. chairman, Ajit Pai, has so far tried to avoid answering in public.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Last April, the chairman of the Federal Communications Commission, Ajit Pai, led the charge for his agency to approve rules allowing television broadcasters to greatly increase the number of stations they own. A few weeks later, Sinclair Broadcasting announced a blockbuster $3.9 billion deal to buy Tribune Media — a deal those new rules made possible.

headline.main: F.C.C. Watchdog Looks Into Changes That Benefited Sinclair
headline.print_headline: F.C.C. Link To Sinclair Is Explored

docs.abstract: It’s the latest state that intends to create a state-run retirement plan for private sector employees without workplace savings accounts.

docs.lead_paragraph: New York is close to joining a growing list of states that are creating a retirement plan option for private sector employees who do not have access to 401(k)-like programs at work.

headline.main: New York Envisions a State-Run Retirement Plan for Private Workers
headline.print_headline: New York  Sets I.R.A. For Those With None

docs.abstract: A federal appeals court ruled that the Labor Department overstepped its authority in requiring financial professionals to act in their clients’ best interests.
docs.snippet: A federal appeals court ruled that the Labor Department overstepped its authority in requiring financial professionals to act in their clients’ best interests.
docs.lead_paragraph: A federal appeals court ruled on Thursday that the Department of Labor overstepped its authority when it wrote a rule that required financial professionals, including brokers and insurance agents, to put their customers’ financial interests ahead of their own.

headline.main: Court Overturns Obama-Era Rule on Retirement Planners

docs.abstract: The cards would hold loan amounts that exceeded tuition, giving borrowers another way to pay expenses — and financial firms a peek at spending patterns.
docs.snippet: The cards would hold loan amounts that exceeded tuition, giving borrowers another way to pay expenses — and financial firms a peek at spending patterns.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Department of Education plans to provide students with a prepaid card that would hold surplus loan money that is not needed for tuition, giving the government and financial services providers a firsthand look at how students are spending those dollars.

headline.print_headline: U.S. Loan Program Plans to Offer Students Prepaid Bank Cards

docs.abstract: After a major breach last year, the credit rating agency promised an app that would make it easy — and free — to lock your credit. It didn’t work.

docs.lead_paragraph: Equifax introduced a free consumer service Wednesday that allows people to lock access to their credit files from a mobile phone. It didn’t work.
